We recommended that management:

	1. Require the Local School Board that the  Annual Budget preparation is confined to program, project and activities chargeable to SEF as those expressly enumerated in Section 4.0 of DEPED-DBM-DILG Joint Memorandum Circular 2017-1;

	2. The concerned officials to validate the SEF budget for consistency with the AIP and APP as required in Article 410 of the IRR of RA 7160;

	3. The concerned officials strictly adhere to the provisions of Section 7.2, 52.1 and 54.1 of the IRR of RA 9184 mandating that all government procurement shall be in accordance with the APP, consistent with its duly approved budget, adherence to the guidelines in the conduct of shopping as the alternative mode of procurement and prohibition of splitting of government contracts.

We recommended that management:

Require the Municipal Budget Officer, Municipal Planning and Development Officer, Municipal Engineer, Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to review the unobligated appropriations of completed proposed PAPs under the 20% local development fund and the availability of such fund balances in the depository bank;

After determining the fund balances in the bank, and in order to maximize utilization of related funds, consider the following courses of action:

Revert the unobligated/unexpended appropriations of completed projects for re-appropriation to other priority development projects;

Require the MPDO to revisit the unfunded priority projects in the development plan or propose new projects for the consideration thereof in the re-appropriation of the unappropriated surplus;

Request the Sangguniang Bayan to pass the related resolutions on the budget to be funded from the unappropriated surplus for the specific priority projects for implementation; and

Execute without delay such projects which are determined to still address the present development needs of the intended beneficiaries.

It is recommended that management:
a. Require the elective/appointed municipal officials and employees to return the livestock without cost to the LGU for dispersal to rightful beneficiaries based on compromise agreement;
b. Conduct alternative solution in the propagation of fowl to generate the desired results in alleviating poverty condition of the constituents;
c. Encourage CSOs/POs to actively participate in all aspects of the BUB project implementation particularly in the procurement and distribution processes.

It is recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

Direct the Municipal Engineer to prepare and maintain a Monthly Monitoring Report to keep track of the progress of all PPAs within his power/jurisdiction from planning stage to implementation to completion since it is one of the duties of the Municipal Engineer to “administer, coordinate, supervise, and control the construction, maintenance, improvement, repair of roads, bridges, and other engineering and public works projects of the local government unit concerned” pursuant to Section 477 of RA 7160; 

Direct the Project Heads/Managers of all non-infrastructure PPAs to prepare and maintain a Monthly Monitoring Report; 

Direct the Municipal Engineer and Project Heads/Managers to coordinate with the Municipal Accountant on the costs incurred of the projects for inclusion in their respective Monthly Monitoring Report; and

Require the Municipal Engineer and other concerned officials to adhere strictly to the provisions of COA Circular No. 2013-004 dated January 30, 2013.

