Recommendation:
We recommend that Management:
Adopt a formal policy setting the rule on: the position titles of officials and employees entitled to mobile expenses and the monthly limit that each qualified official may be entitled to with consideration on the economical, corporate plan offered by mobile phone companies that will suit the needs of the LGU instead of the current practice of allocating without basis an excessive monthly budget of P3,000.00 per office or official;
Refrain from charging mobile expenses against the Petty Cash Fund;
Deactivate the accounts which were availed of by LGU officials or employees who are no longer in service as well as those accounts where the subscribers are not LGU employees or officials;
Revisit the provisions of COA Circular 2012-003 with its Annex D whereby only one unit of mobile phone is allowed for each entitled official which shall not be lower than the Division Chief rank;
Issue Acknowledgement Receipt of Equipment for mobile units where the costs of which were incorporated in the post-paid subscription plans availed of by the entitled officials of the LGU since these were paid out of the government funds; and
Provide COA with machine copies of ORs which were printed in glossy papers as well as Billing Statements to support the claim for mobile expenses.

